Goal
- create boilerplate project with backend, frontend, db
- setup in server
- make it easy to run locally (set up dev environment)
- setup pipeline

STEPS
- project local setup
  - folder structure
  - .gitignore
  - docker-compose
  - empty readme

- frontend setup
  - new react app with sh
  - copy Dockerfile

- backend setup
  - extract zip
  - copy Dockerfile
  - application.properties

- db setup
  - tel user to confirm 'y' that local and remote db servers are running
  - create db on local server
  - create db on remote server

- setup nginx
  - get nginx file on docker on server
  - add routes for frontend and backend
  - reload nginx

- env files
  - create in local folder (will be git/docker ignored)
    - (db already exists)
    - backend
    - frontend (do later)
  - on server

- github setup
  - create repository

- setup dev environment:
  - application.properties/.env
  - localbuild.sh?

- docker ignore
  - create
  - push

- pipeline
  - create push

Notes
- ignore env files where necessary (dockerhub, git)
- docker hub setup not necessary, will do it automatically through pipeline
- not necessary to copy .env files with gh actions. just place them where they should be beforehand
- set href when building frontend
- change container name to be project specific, not just "frontend"/"backend"
- make sure pipeline doesnt stop/remove docker resources of other apps